post /v1/apps/{application-id}/campaigns
(createCampaign)

Path Parameter — The unique identifier for the application. This identifier is displayed as the Project ID on the Amazon Pinpoint console. default: null

post /v1/templates/{template-name}/email
(createEmailTemplate)
Creates a message template for messages that are sent through the email channel.

Path parameters

template-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the message template. A template name must start with an alphanumeric character and can contain a maximum of 128 characters. The characters can be alphanumeric characters, underscores (_), or hyphens (-). Template names are case sensitive. default: null

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

delete /v1/templates/{template-name}/email
(deleteEmailTemplate)
Deletes a message template for messages that were sent through the email channel.

Path parameters

template-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the message template. A template name must start with an alphanumeric character and can contain a maximum of 128 characters. The characters can be alphanumeric characters, underscores (_), or hyphens (-). Template names are case sensitive. default: null

Request headers

X-Amz-Content-Sha256 (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Date (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Algorithm (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Credential (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Security-Token (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Signature (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-SignedHeaders (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null

Query parameters

version (optional)
Query Parameter —

The unique identifier for the version of the message template to update, retrieve information about, or delete. To retrieve identifiers and other information for all the versions of a template, use the Template Versions resource.

If specified, this value must match the identifier for an existing template version. If specified for an update operation, this value must match the identifier for the latest existing version of the template. This restriction helps ensure that race conditions don't occur.

If you don't specify a value for this parameter, Amazon Pinpoint does the following:

  • For a get operation, retrieves information about the active version of the template.

  • For an update operation, saves the updates to (overwrites) the latest existing version of the template, if the create-new-version parameter isn't used or is set to false.

  • For a delete operation, deletes the template, including all versions of the template.

default: null

Return type

DeleteEmailTemplateResponse

Example data

{
  "MessageBody" : {
    "Message" : "",
    "RequestID" : ""
  }

(deleteSmsTemplate)

Path Parameter — The name of the message template. A template name must start with an alphanumeric character and can contain a maximum of 128 characters. The characters can be alphanumeric characters, underscores (_), or hyphens (-). Template names are case sensitive. default: null

Request headers

X-Amz-Content-Sha256 (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Date (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Algorithm (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Credential (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Security-Token (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Signature (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-SignedHeaders (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null

Query parameters

version (optional)
Query Parameter —

The unique identifier for the version of the message template to update, retrieve information about, or delete. To retrieve identifiers and other information for all the versions of a template, use the Template Versions resource.

If specified, this value must match the identifier for an existing template version. If specified for an update operation, this value must match the identifier for the latest existing version of the template. This restriction helps ensure that race conditions don't occur.

If you don't specify a value for this parameter, Amazon Pinpoint does the following:

  • For a get operation, retrieves information about the active version of the template.

  • For an update operation, saves the updates to (overwrites) the latest existing version of the template, if the create-new-version parameter isn't used or is set to false.

  • For a delete operation, deletes the template, including all versions of the template.

default: null

get /v1/apps/{application-id}/kpis/daterange/{kpi-name}
(getApplicationDateRangeKpi)
Retrieves (queries) pre-aggregated data for a standard metric that applies to an application.

Path parameters

application-id (required)
Path Parameter — The unique identifier for the application. This identifier is displayed as the Project ID on the Amazon Pinpoint console. default: null
kpi-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the metric, also referred to as a key performance indicator (KPI), to retrieve data for. This value describes the associated metric and consists of two or more terms, which are comprised of lowercase alphanumeric characters, separated by a hyphen. Examples are email-open-rate and successful-delivery-rate. For a list of valid values, see the Amazon Pinpoint Developer Guide. default: null

Request headers

X-Amz-Content-Sha256 (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Date (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Algorithm (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Credential (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Security-Token (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Signature (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-SignedHeaders (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null

Query parameters

end-time (optional)
Query Parameter — The last date and time to retrieve data for, as part of an inclusive date range that filters the query results. This value should be in extended ISO 8601 format and use Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), for example: 2019-07-26T20:00:00Z for 8:00 PM UTC July 26, 2019. default: null format: date-time
next-token (optional)
Query Parameter — The string that specifies which page of results to return in a paginated response. This parameter is not supported for application, campaign, and journey metrics. default: null
page-size (optional)
Query Parameter — The maximum number of items to include in each page of a paginated response. This parameter is not supported for application, campaign, and journey metrics. default: null
start-time (optional)
Query Parameter — The first date and time to retrieve data for, as part of an inclusive date range that filters the query results. This value should be in extended ISO 8601 format and use Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), for example: 2019-07-19T20:00:00Z for 8:00 PM UTC July 19, 2019. This value should also be fewer than 90 days from the current day. default: null format: date-time

get /v1/apps/{application-id}/campaigns/{campaign-id}/kpis/daterange/{kpi-name}
(getCampaignDateRangeKpi)
Retrieves (queries) pre-aggregated data for a standard metric that applies to a campaign.

Path parameters

application-id (required)
Path Parameter — The unique identifier for the application. This identifier is displayed as the Project ID on the Amazon Pinpoint console. default: null
campaign-id (required)
Path Parameter — The unique identifier for the campaign. default: null
kpi-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the metric, also referred to as a key performance indicator (KPI), to retrieve data for. This value describes the associated metric and consists of two or more terms, which are comprised of lowercase alphanumeric characters, separated by a hyphen. Examples are email-open-rate and successful-delivery-rate. For a list of valid values, see the Amazon Pinpoint Developer Guide. default: null

Request headers

X-Amz-Content-Sha256 (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Date (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Algorithm (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Credential (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Security-Token (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Signature (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-SignedHeaders (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null

Query parameters

end-time (optional)
Query Parameter — The last date and time to retrieve data for, as part of an inclusive date range that filters the query results. This value should be in extended ISO 8601 format and use Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), for example: 2019-07-26T20:00:00Z for 8:00 PM UTC July 26, 2019. default: null format: date-time
next-token (optional)
Query Parameter — The string that specifies which page of results to return in a paginated response. This parameter is not supported for application, campaign, and journey metrics. default: null
page-size (optional)
Query Parameter — The maximum number of items to include in each page of a paginated response. This parameter is not supported for application, campaign, and journey metrics. default: null
start-time (optional)
Query Parameter — The first date and time to retrieve data for, as part of an inclusive date range that filters the query results. This value should be in extended ISO 8601 format and use Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), for example: 2019-07-19T20:00:00Z for 8:00 PM UTC July 19, 2019. This value should also be fewer than 90 days from the current day. default: null format: date-time

Return type

    "CampaignId" : "",
    "StartTime" : "",
    "ApplicationId" : ""
  }
}

get /v1/templates/{template-name}/email
(getEmailTemplate)
Retrieves the content and settings of a message template for messages that are sent through the email channel.

Path parameters

template-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the message template. A template name must start with an alphanumeric character and can contain a maximum of 128 characters. The characters can be alphanumeric characters, underscores (_), or hyphens (-). Template names are case sensitive. default: null

Request headers

X-Amz-Content-Sha256 (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Date (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Algorithm (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Credential (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Security-Token (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Signature (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-SignedHeaders (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null

Query parameters

version (optional)
Query Parameter —

The unique identifier for the version of the message template to update, retrieve information about, or delete. To retrieve identifiers and other information for all the versions of a template, use the Template Versions resource.

If specified, this value must match the identifier for an existing template version. If specified for an update operation, this value must match the identifier for the latest existing version of the template. This restriction helps ensure that race conditions don't occur.

If you don't specify a value for this parameter, Amazon Pinpoint does the following:

  • For a get operation, retrieves information about the active version of the template.

  • For an update operation, saves the updates to (overwrites) the latest existing version of the template, if the create-new-version parameter isn't used or is set to false.

  • For a delete operation, deletes the template, including all versions of the template.

default: null

Return type

Example data

{
  "EmailTemplateResponse" : {
    "CreationDate" : "",
    "HtmlPart" : "",

    "tags" : "",
    "RecommenderId" : "",

    "DefaultSubstitutions" : "",
    "Arn" : ""
  }
}

(getJourneyDateRangeKpi)
Retrieves (queries) pre-aggregated data for a standard engagement metric that applies to a journey.

Path parameters

application-id (required)
Path Parameter — The unique identifier for the application. This identifier is displayed as the Project ID on the Amazon Pinpoint console. default: null
journey-id (required)
Path Parameter — The unique identifier for the journey. default: null
kpi-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the metric, also referred to as a key performance indicator (KPI), to retrieve data for. This value describes the associated metric and consists of two or more terms, which are comprised of lowercase alphanumeric characters, separated by a hyphen. Examples are email-open-rate and successful-delivery-rate. For a list of valid values, see the Amazon Pinpoint Developer Guide. default: null

Header Parameter — default: null

end-time (optional)
Query Parameter — The last date and time to retrieve data for, as part of an inclusive date range that filters the query results. This value should be in extended ISO 8601 format and use Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), for example: 2019-07-26T20:00:00Z for 8:00 PM UTC July 26, 2019. default: null format: date-time
next-token (optional)
Query Parameter — The string that specifies which page of results to return in a paginated response. This parameter is not supported for application, campaign, and journey metrics. default: null
page-size (optional)
Query Parameter — The maximum number of items to include in each page of a paginated response. This parameter is not supported for application, campaign, and journey metrics. default: null
start-time (optional)
Query Parameter — The first date and time to retrieve data for, as part of an inclusive date range that filters the query results. This value should be in extended ISO 8601 format and use Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), for example: 2019-07-19T20:00:00Z for 8:00 PM UTC July 19, 2019. This value should also be fewer than 90 days from the current day. default: null format: date-time

get /v1/templates/{template-name}/push
(getPushTemplate)
Retrieves the content and settings of a message template for messages that are sent through a push notification channel.

Path parameters

template-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the message template. A template name must start with an alphanumeric character and can contain a maximum of 128 characters. The characters can be alphanumeric characters, underscores (_), or hyphens (-). Template names are case sensitive. default: null

Request headers

X-Amz-Content-Sha256 (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Date (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Algorithm (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Credential (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Security-Token (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Signature (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-SignedHeaders (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null

Query parameters

version (optional)
Query Parameter —

The unique identifier for the version of the message template to update, retrieve information about, or delete. To retrieve identifiers and other information for all the versions of a template, use the Template Versions resource.

If specified, this value must match the identifier for an existing template version. If specified for an update operation, this value must match the identifier for the latest existing version of the template. This restriction helps ensure that race conditions don't occur.

If you don't specify a value for this parameter, Amazon Pinpoint does the following:

  • For a get operation, retrieves information about the active version of the template.

  • For an update operation, saves the updates to (overwrites) the latest existing version of the template, if the create-new-version parameter isn't used or is set to false.

  • For a delete operation, deletes the template, including all versions of the template.

default: null

get /v1/templates/{template-name}/sms
(getSmsTemplate)
Retrieves the content and settings of a message template for messages that are sent through the SMS channel.

Path parameters

template-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the message template. A template name must start with an alphanumeric character and can contain a maximum of 128 characters. The characters can be alphanumeric characters, underscores (_), or hyphens (-). Template names are case sensitive. default: null

Request headers

X-Amz-Content-Sha256 (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Date (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Algorithm (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Credential (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Security-Token (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Signature (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-SignedHeaders (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null

Query parameters

version (optional)
Query Parameter —

The unique identifier for the version of the message template to update, retrieve information about, or delete. To retrieve identifiers and other information for all the versions of a template, use the Template Versions resource.

If specified, this value must match the identifier for an existing template version. If specified for an update operation, this value must match the identifier for the latest existing version of the template. This restriction helps ensure that race conditions don't occur.

If you don't specify a value for this parameter, Amazon Pinpoint does the following:

  • For a get operation, retrieves information about the active version of the template.

  • For an update operation, saves the updates to (overwrites) the latest existing version of the template, if the create-new-version parameter isn't used or is set to false.

  • For a delete operation, deletes the template, including all versions of the template.

default: null

Return type

put /v1/apps/{application-id}/attributes/{attribute-type}
(removeAttributes)
Removes one or more attributes, of the same attribute type, from all the endpoints that are associated with an application.

Path parameters

application-id (required)
Path Parameter — The unique identifier for the application. This identifier is displayed as the Project ID on the Amazon Pinpoint console. default: null
attribute-type (required)
Path Parameter —

The type of attribute or attributes to remove. Valid values are:

  • endpoint-custom-attributes - Custom attributes that describe endpoints, such as the date when an associated user opted in or out of receiving communications from you through a specific type of channel.

  • endpoint-metric-attributes - Custom metrics that your app reports to Amazon Pinpoint for endpoints, such as the number of app sessions or the number of items left in a cart.

  • endpoint-user-attributes - Custom attributes that describe users, such as first name, last name, and age.

default: null

put /v1/templates/{template-name}/email
(updateEmailTemplate)
Updates an existing message template for messages that are sent through the email channel.

Path parameters

template-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the message template. A template name must start with an alphanumeric character and can contain a maximum of 128 characters. The characters can be alphanumeric characters, underscores (_), or hyphens (-). Template names are case sensitive. default: null

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

Request body

UpdateEmailTemplate_request UpdateEmailTemplate_request (required)
Body Parameter —

Request headers

X-Amz-Content-Sha256 (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Date (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Algorithm (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Credential (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Security-Token (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Signature (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-SignedHeaders (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null

Query parameters

create-new-version (optional)
Query Parameter —

Specifies whether to save the updates as a new version of the message template. Valid values are: true, save the updates as a new version; and, false, save the updates to (overwrite) the latest existing version of the template.

If you don't specify a value for this parameter, Amazon Pinpoint saves the updates to (overwrites) the latest existing version of the template. If you specify a value of true for this parameter, don't specify a value for the version parameter. Otherwise, an error will occur.

default: null
version (optional)
Query Parameter —

The unique identifier for the version of the message template to update, retrieve information about, or delete. To retrieve identifiers and other information for all the versions of a template, use the Template Versions resource.

If specified, this value must match the identifier for an existing template version. If specified for an update operation, this value must match the identifier for the latest existing version of the template. This restriction helps ensure that race conditions don't occur.

If you don't specify a value for this parameter, Amazon Pinpoint does the following:

  • For a get operation, retrieves information about the active version of the template.

  • For an update operation, saves the updates to (overwrites) the latest existing version of the template, if the create-new-version parameter isn't used or is set to false.

  • For a delete operation, deletes the template, including all versions of the template.

default: null

Return type

UpdateEmailTemplateResponse

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "MessageBody" : {
    "Message" : "",
    "RequestID" : ""
  }
}

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

202

Success UpdateEmailTemplateResponse

480

BadRequestException oas_any_type_not_mapped

481

InternalServerErrorException oas_any_type_not_mapped

482

PayloadTooLargeException oas_any_type_not_mapped

484

Up 
put /v1/templates/{template-name}/push
(updatePushTemplate)
Updates an existing message template for messages that are sent through a push notification channel.

Path parameters

template-name (required)
Path Parameter — The name of the message template. A template name must start with an alphanumeric character and can contain a maximum of 128 characters. The characters can be alphanumeric characters, underscores (_), or hyphens (-). Template names are case sensitive. default: null

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

Request body

UpdatePushTemplate_request UpdatePushTemplate_request (required)
Body Parameter —

Request headers

X-Amz-Content-Sha256 (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Date (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Algorithm (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Credential (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Security-Token (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-Signature (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null
X-Amz-SignedHeaders (optional)
Header Parameter — default: null

Query parameters

create-new-version (optional)
Query Parameter —

Specifies whether to save the updates as a new version of the message template. Valid values are: true, save the updates as a new version; and, false, save the updates to (overwrite) the latest existing version of the template.

If you don't specify a value for this parameter, Amazon Pinpoint saves the updates to (overwrites) the latest existing version of the template. If you specify a value of true for this parameter, don't specify a value for the version parameter. Otherwise, an error will occur.

default: null
version (optional)
Query Parameter —

The unique identifier for the version of the message template to update, retrieve information about, or delete. To retrieve identifiers and other information for all the versions of a template, use the Template Versions resource.

If specified, this value must match the identifier for an existing template version. If specified for an update operation, this value must match the identifier for the latest existing version of the template. This restriction helps ensure that race conditions don't occur.

If you don't specify a value for this parameter, Amazon Pinpoint does the following:

  • For a get operation, retrieves information about the active version of the template.

  • For an update operation, saves the updates to (overwrites) the latest existing version of the template, if the create-new-version parameter isn't used or is set to false.

  • For a delete operation, deletes the template, including all versions of the template.

default: null

Return type

UpdatePushTemplateResponse

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "MessageBody" : {
    "Message" : "",
    "RequestID" : ""
  }
}

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

202

Success UpdatePushTemplateResponse

Specifies the settings for a multivariate split activity in a journey. This type of activity sends participants down one of as many as five paths (including a default Else path) in a journey, based on conditions that you specify.

To create multivariate split activities that send participants down different paths based on push notification events (such as Open or Received events), your mobile app has to specify the User ID and Endpoint ID values.
